S'With the Lloyds TSB Mobile Banking app, it\xe2\x80\x99s even easier to manage your Lloyds TSB UK personal accounts on the move.Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app.  \xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble logging on should log on from their mobile browser by visiting www.lloydstsb.com and selecting Personal Log On.We apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused. We\xe2\x80\x99re working to release a further update to address these issues as soon as possible.Updates in Version 2.0\xe2\x80\xa2 Fix to help repair the crashing and connectivity issues that some users have been experiencingBased on your feedback, we\xe2\x80\x99ve made these additional improvements to Mobile Banking:\xe2\x80\xa2 View a longer transaction history \xe2\x80\xa2 Register for Internet Banking\xe2\x80\xa2 Change some of your personal details\xe2\x80\xa2 Manage your existing overdraftsEven if you\xe2\x80\x99re not a Lloyds TSB customer, you can use the app to find any Lloyds TSB branch or Cashpoint \xc2\xae and LINK ATMs in the UK. With the latest updates, you can now:\xe2\x80\xa2 Find a Lloyds TSB branch or Cashpoint\xc2\xae or LINK ATM in the UK\xe2\x80\xa2 Log on with your usual Internet Banking details\xe2\x80\xa2 View balances and transaction history \xe2\x80\xa2 Check your credit card limit\xe2\x80\xa2 Make transfers between your Lloyds TSB UK personal current and savings accounts\xe2\x80\xa2 Set up and make payments \xe2\x80\xa2 Find useful Lloyds TSB phone numbers- And enjoy a high level of security.You don\xe2\x80\x99t need to register to use the app\xe2\x80\x99s Mobile Banking services if you\xe2\x80\x99re already a Lloyds TSB personal Internet Banking customer. Simply log on with your usual details wherever you have signal. If you haven\xe2\x80\x99t registered for Internet Banking yet, you can do it through the app.Keeping you safe onlineWe use the latest online security measures to protect your money, your personal information and your privacy.And our online guarantee means we\xe2\x80\x99ll refund your money in the unlikely event you experience a fraud when using this app as long as you\xe2\x80\x99ve been careful (for example, kept your security details safe).Some things you can do to help protect yourself when using this app:\xe2\x80\xa2 Treat mobile security as seriously as you treat computer security.\xe2\x80\xa2 Take care when entering personal information in public places.\xe2\x80\xa2 Find out what software your phone provider offers to protect you online.\xe2\x80\xa2 Switch off Bluetooth when you\xe2\x80\x99re not using it\xe2\x80\xa2 Don\xe2\x80\x99t accept or open any applications or MMS messages from unknown senders \xe2\x80\xa2 Use your mobile phone\xe2\x80\x99s security lock or PINImportant information This app and Mobile Banking are designed for use in the UK. We don\xe2\x80\x99t charge you for using this app but your mobile operator may charge for some services.  Services may be affected by phone signal and functionality.The Branch/ATM finder uses location based services.  We, LINK Scheme and/or Google may get data about your location (i.e. GPS signals from your mobile device) or data that can be used to approximate your location (such as your mobile ID).The Mobile Banking service in this app is available to our UK personal Internet Banking customers only. Use of it is subject to our website terms and conditions and Internet Banking terms and conditions. http://www.lloydstsb.com/legal.asp By using this app or providing information to us, you consent to the use and transfer of your information as set out above and in our privacy policy. www.lloydstsb.com/privacy2.aspCashpoint\xc2\xae is a registered trademark of Lloyds TSB Bank plc.This app and Mobile Banking are operated by Lloyds TSB Bank plc (registered in England and Wales (no. 2065), registered office: 25 Gresham Street, London EC2V 7HN) and Lloyds TSB Scotland plc (registered in Scotland (No.SC095237), Registered office: Henry Duncan House, 120 George Street, Edinburgh EH2 4LH. Authorised and regulated by the Financial Services Authority.Recent changes:Following the release of version 2.0, some customers have reported problems with the app.\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers updating from a previous version may find the app icon displays incorrectly on the home screen, or disappears. If this happens, please look on your phone\xe2\x80\x99s full app menu to find it\xe2\x80\xa2 Customers having trouble logging on should log on from their mobile browser by visiting www.lloydstsb.comWe apologise for any inconvenience we may have caused, and are working to release a fix asap.'
